entries.femaleVariant: Ey, 'ey, 'ey, V! Wait a sec!
Listen to that guy. How'd you rate his chops?
Could stand a little more stage presence, fingering's all wrong, loses the tempo more than he keeps it, but – not bad.
Really know how to give a guy a compliment.
That how you got your start? Street busker with big dreams?
entries.maleVariant: Is that how you got your start? Street busker with big dreams?

entries.femaleVariant: Don't make me laugh. No time for playin' my way to the top. Was too busy shakin' the world awake.
Had an audience from the start. Some recorded our stuff, didn't even know who we were.
Jokes aside. Think those tapes still exist? After all these years?
entries.maleVariant: Jokes aside. You think those tapes still exist? After all these years?

entries.femaleVariant: Hmm... Y'know, Rainbow Cadenza's not far from here. Club we played till the band fell apart.
Weak. Amateur hour.
Not bad. I guess.
Ugh. Pathetic. Can barely hold the thing. I ain't a musician, but even I can tell that's sloppy stuff.
To my untrained ear, sounds all right, I guess. Easy listenin', at least.
entries.maleVariant: To my untrained ear, sounds all right, I guess. I mean, it's easy listenin', at least.

entries.femaleVariant: Ladies and gentlemen, a critic. Chill, choomba. Ain't half bad.
Know why? Technique's second-rate. But the feeling – that's what counts.
Bein' at the top can be worth it. Wanna shake the world, y'know... World's gotta feel you first.
entries.maleVariant: Bein' at the top can be worth it. You wanna shake the world, y'know... Heh. Well, world's gotta feel you first.

entries.femaleVariant: All right, princess. Least you played some gigs. Saw those memories of yours.
True. Played where we could. Parks, old factories, underground clubs...
Success gives you a platform.
Losers tend to say that.
Oh-ho-ho. Ooh – isn't that what every failed "artist" says about their work?
entries.maleVariant: Oh-ho-ho. Now isn't that what every failed "artist" says about their work?

entries.femaleVariant: Old tapes could be worth somethin'...
Lemme find those tapes, I'll be your fan.
So you're sayin' some old Samurai bootlegs are still floatin' around town? I smell eds...
entries.maleVariant: So you're sayin' some old Samurai bootlegs are still floatin' around town? Ooh, I smell eds...

entries.femaleVariant: Ooh! Mean to say I could get my hands on some old Samurai bootlegs?
No idea you were such a materialist. Could almost cry. Almost.
Just you fuckin' try.
Guy's hurtin', got somethin' he can't take. And it shows.
And you pay for it. You spend your lyrics layin' waste to the big record corps, who's gonna sign you then?
But give up your ideals, and no amount of eddies can buy 'em back.
Know what? You're right – I failed. Corpo-tyrants still run this town, just like fifty years ago.
But if you think in my heart of hearts I wanna be the next teen idol, think again. Don't give half a fuck about that commercial shit!
I'm 'onna find those tapes, I'm 'onna shriek like a little fangirl any time you open your mouth. Happy?
Great spot. Place for people with their heads on straight. Maybe they'll know somethin'.
